<subSubSection lastPageId="171" lastPageNumber="172" pageId="170" pageNumber="171" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="170" pageNumber="171">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="170" pageNumber="171">
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 155" captionStartId="F155" captionText="Figure 155. Distribution of Conostegia foreroi." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.67.6703.figure155" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/96513" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">155</figureCitation>
). Endemic to the the departments of Antioquia and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Chocó">Choco</normalizedToken>
in Colombia, 1300-1400 m in elevation.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-Zenodo-Dep="973961" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.67.6703.figure155" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/96513" pageId="170" pageNumber="171" start="Figure 155" startId="F155">
<paragraph pageId="170" pageNumber="171">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">Figure 155.</emphasis>
Distribution of 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Wurdack" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia foreroi" order="Myrtales" pageId="170" pageNumber="171" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="foreroi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">Conostegia foreroi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph pageId="171" pageNumber="172">
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Wurdack" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia foreroi" order="Myrtales" pageId="171" pageNumber="172" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="foreroi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">
<pageBreakToken pageId="171" pageNumber="172" start="start">Conostegia</pageBreakToken>
foreroi
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a very uncommon species characterized by its dense pubescence on stems, leaves, inflorescences and hypanthia. As 
<bibRefCitation author="Wurdack, JJ" journalOrPublisher="Phytologia" pageId="244" pageNumber="245" pagination="293 - 301" refId="B89" refString="Wurdack, JJ, 1988. Certamen Melastomataceis XXXVIII. Phytologia 64 (4): 293 - 301" title="Certamen Melastomataceis XXXVIII." volume="64" year="1988">Wurdack (1988)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned in the protologue, it resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="D.Don, 1823" authorityName="D.Don" authorityYear="1823" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomaceae" genus="Clidemia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Clidemia costaricensis" order="Myrtales" pageId="171" pageNumber="172" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="costaricensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">Clidemia costaricensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="D.Don, 1823" authorityName="D.Don" authorityYear="1823" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomaceae" genus="Clidemia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Clidemia petiolaris" order="Myrtales" pageId="171" pageNumber="172" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="petiolaris">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">Clidemia petiolaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The latter two species thus also resemble each other but none of the three are closely related based on the molecular phylogeny, evidencing the possible multiple evolutions of shrubby and densely pubescent species. Among the differences between 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Wurdack" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia foreroi" order="Myrtales" pageId="171" pageNumber="172" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="foreroi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">Conostegia foreroi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that help distinguish it from 
<taxonomicName authority="D.Don, 1823" authorityName="D.Don" authorityYear="1823" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomaceae" genus="Clidemia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Clidemia costaricensis" order="Myrtales" pageId="171" pageNumber="172" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="costaricensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">Clidemia costaricensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="D.Don, 1823" authorityName="D.Don" authorityYear="1823" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomaceae" genus="Clidemia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Clidemia petiolaris" order="Myrtales" pageId="171" pageNumber="172" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="petiolaris">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">Clidemia petiolaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are the flattened setae on the nodes, smaller flowers, a sparsely glandular pubescent ovary apex and stamens that have a stronger geniculation. Within section 
<taxonomicName authority="D.Don, 1823" authorityName="D.Don" authorityYear="1823" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomaceae" genus="Clidemia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Myrtales" pageId="171" pageNumber="172" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Geniculatae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">Geniculatae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Wurdack" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia foreroi" order="Myrtales" pageId="171" pageNumber="172" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="foreroi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">Conostegia foreroi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appears to resemble more 
<taxonomicName authority="D.Don, 1823" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Kriebel" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomaceae" genus="Clidemia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Clidemia hammelii" order="Myrtales" pageId="171" pageNumber="172" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hammelii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">Clidemia hammelii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The latter species is overall less pubescent and has pocket domatia at the base of the leaf on the abaxial surface. This species appears to also converges with 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Kriebel" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia trichosantha" order="Myrtales" pageId="171" pageNumber="172" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="trichosantha">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">Conostegia trichosantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the accumulation of water on the external pubescence of the floral buds. The paratype 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">
Lozano and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Díaz">Diaz</normalizedToken>
3201
</emphasis>
(US) notes extreme herbivory on the plant like in other species of section 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Myrtales" pageId="171" pageNumber="172" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Geniculatae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">Geniculatae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
such as 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Kriebel" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia calocoma" order="Myrtales" pageId="171" pageNumber="172" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="calocoma">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">Conostegia calocoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
